classes.name: aqua
classes.description: Like a cardio class but in the pool, Aqua is perfect if you’re just starting your fitness journey, or coming back from an injury. This class works your heart and lungs, but gives your joints a break.

classes.name: cycle power
classes.description: A performance based cycle class that brings the euphoric highs of riding outdoors into a music driven studio. Track your personal bests and create your own benchmark for success!

classes.name: cycle tempo
classes.description: Ride to the beat and get lost in the music. If upper body movement is your thing, you can groove along to some uplifting tunes or you can just ride – whatever gets you moving.

classes.name: lift club
classes.description: Build your strength and develop your technique in our Lift Club class.

classes.name: move club
classes.description: Stay active through low-intensity movement in a group class made for mature adults or those recovering from injury.

classes.name: pilates align.
classes.description: Focus on improving posture and muscular imbalances, increasing mobility in joints and deepening core strength. The class uses principles of Joseph Pilates to improve posture, function and form.

classes.name: pilates athletic.
classes.description: An athletic Pilates Matwork class designed to sculpt, tone and define the body. Challenge your perception of a Pilates class with a focus on endurance.

classes.name: reformer align
classes.description: Expand and build on the skills you've learned in Reformer Foundations. Using functional moves and classic Reformer Pilates, you'll leave our class feeling more connected to your body and stable on your own two feet. Don't forget your grip socks.

classes.name: reformer athletic
classes.description: Are you looking to take your training to the next level? If you are a regular class-goer and know how to use the equipment, you'll gain new skills and get the workout your body needs. Don't forget your grip socks.

classes.name: reformer foundations
classes.description: Enjoy a full-body workout as you learn Reformer Pilates techniques.

classes.name: reformer recovery
classes.description: In our signature Reformer Recovery class, you will be guided through a variety of stretches that soften and lengthen tissues and fibres in all the right places.

classes.name: sound bath
classes.description: Take a journey into sound healing with Sound Bath. Set to the soothing sounds of crystal singing bowls, this practice offers you space to nap without guilt. Starting with an opening pose and the remainder of the class in absolute rest, this is the ultimate occasion to recover, rebalance and reset.

classes.name: strength and conditioning
classes.description: Mix high-intensity training and functional movement in Strength and Conditioning. Expect a blend of dumbbells, kettlebells and Echo bikes for a workout that’s always switching things up.

classes.name: swim club
classes.description: If you're a keen swimmer looking to join a group of like-minded people for a casual swim or to improve your pacing, join our Swim Club. With the help of our official Virgin Active coaches, you'll join a community of swimmers in the pool.

classes.name: yoga align
classes.description: Test your endurance and build confidence as you move into alignment.

classes.name: yoga calm
classes.description: In this slow-paced class, you will release tension, target deep connective tissues, like ligaments and tendons to increase circulation in your joints, which will improve your flexibility.

classes.name: yoga flow
classes.description: Raise your vibration in Flow, a high-energy, fast-paced class. Through dynamic poses, you'll build mobility and enhance your muscle development.

classes.name: yoga foundations
classes.description: Whether you’re new to yoga or it’s been a while since you rolled out your mat, our Yoga foundations class is ideal for those who want to take things at a gentle pace.
